cs.HC, cs.SI, cs.GR, cs.CE, cs.SE

The paper focuses on the development of a visualization system for interactive exploration of parameter spaces of multi-variate simulation models. This involves analyzing current practices of domain experts, deriving design requirements, and conducting in-depth case studies. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC), followed by Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) as the system involves exploring and partitioning parameter spaces. Graphics (cs.GR) is also a likely sub-category as the system involves visualization. Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science (cs.CE) and Software Engineering (cs.SE) are also possible sub-categories as the system involves developing and testing simulation models.
